The paper deals with topics related to computational complexity, logic, and information theory. Specifically, it discusses the strength of theories in bounded arithmetic and their relationship to proof complexity. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also touches upon topics related to data structures (cs.DS), cryptography (cs.CR), and information theory (cs.IT), which makes these sub-categories likely as well.
